A format screw, by someone who hates format screws.

This CorpseCon entry was a tough one to write. The conprocs pushed the article hard into a writing style I'm not comfortable with at all.

Thanks to Tyumen and others for crit!

+notes

-notes


For the court summons at the end, I used two official court summons as a template: one from the US District Court system, and one from the state of New York. Both of these documents are public domain, and I believe that I have modified it enough that what is in the article is distinct from either source; however, something may have slipped through the cracks and I would like this on record in case it comes up.

Also, because I know somebody will probably bring it up, the 555 number does not exist as that area code is reserved. It's actually a fairly common practice to give a fictional number that area code so nobody gets called by curious readers.








